nodes.documentation:
@dev Marks an address as being approved for transferFrom(), overwriting any previous
  approval. Setting _approved to address(0) clears all transfer approval.
  NOTE: _approve() does NOT send the Approval event. This is intentional because
  _approve() and transferFrom() are used together for putting Gaos on auction, and
  there is no value in spamming the log with Approval events in that case.

params._to: The address to be granted transfer approval. Pass address(0) to  clear all approvals.
params._tokenId: The ID of the Gao that can be transferred if this call succeeds.

tokensOfOwner(address).details: This method MUST NEVER be called by smart contract code. First, it's fairly  expensive (it walks the entire Gao array looking for gaos belonging to owner),  but it also returns a dynamic array, which is only supported for web3 calls, and  not contract-to-contract calls.

params._owner: The owner whose Gaos we are interested in.

params._to: The address of the recipient, can be a user or contract.
params._tokenId: The ID of the Gao to transfer.

params._from: The address that owns the Gao to be transfered.
params._to: The address that should take ownership of the Gao. Can be any address,  including the caller.
params._tokenId: The ID of the Gao to be transferred.

approve(address,uint256).notice: Grant another address the right to transfer a specific Gao via  transferFrom(). This is the preferred flow for transfering NFTs to contracts.

balanceOf(address).notice: Returns the number of Gaos owned by a specific address.

ownerOf(uint256).notice: Returns the address currently assigned ownership of a given Gao.

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Introspection interface as per ERC-165 (https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/issues/165).  Returns true for any standardized interfaces implemented by this contract. We implement  ERC-165 (obviously!) and ERC-721.

tokensOfOwner(address).notice: Returns a list of all Gao IDs assigned to an address.

totalSupply().notice: Returns the total number of Gaos currently in existence.

transfer(address,uint256).notice: Transfers a Gao to another address. If transferring to a smart  contract be VERY CAREFUL to ensure that it is aware of ERC-721 (or  CryptoGaos specifically) or your Gao may be lost forever. Seriously.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: Transfer a Gao owned by another address, for which the calling address  has previously been granted transfer approval by the owner.
